---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Body Words — Highest Scoring Anatomy Vocabulary"
  description="Top body and anatomy words valid in Scrabble ranked by score. PHARYNX (22pts), THORAX (16pts), LARYNX (16pts), SPLEEN (8pts), KIDNEY (14pts), ELBOW (10pts). Free word finder."
  keywords="scrabble body words, pharynx scrabble points, thorax scrabble, larynx scrabble word, anatomy scrabble words, body part scrabble, high scoring body words, medical scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Body Words — Highest Scoring Anatomy Vocabulary",
    "description": "Top body and anatomy words valid in Scrabble ranked by score. PHARYNX (22pts), THORAX (16pts), LARYNX (16pts), SPLEEN (8pts), KIDNEY (14pts), ELBOW (10pts).",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-body-words" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the highest scoring body word in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PHARYNX scores 22 points (P=3, H=4, A=1, R=1, Y=4, N=1, X=8). The X tile at the end provides 8 points, and the combination of H and Y adds another 8. It refers to the cavity behind the nose and mouth connecting to the esophagus." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is THORAX a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, THORAX is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 16 points (T=1, H=4, O=1, R=1, A=1, X=8). It means the chest area between the neck and abdomen. The X at the end gives it strong scoring power." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What body words use X in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "PHARYNX (22pts), THORAX (16pts), and LARYNX (16pts) all end in X, which is worth 8 points. These -YNX and -AX endings are powerful because X is hard to play elsewhere, and these words use common surrounding tiles." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Body Words — Highest Scoring Anatomy Vocabulary</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Your anatomy knowledge is a secret weapon in Scrabble. Body words often end in high-value letters like X and use consonant clusters that clear awkward racks. From PHARYNX to ELBOW, here are the body words that score big.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">22 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PHARYNX (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">86 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Combined Top 6</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words with X</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 6 Body Words by Score</h2>
      <p>These anatomy words deliver the highest base scores. Three of them end in X — making them essential plays when you're holding that 8-point tile.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">PHARYNX — 22 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, H=4, A=1, R=1, Y=4, N=1, X=8 · 7 letters · Bingo eligible</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The throat cavity behind your nose. As a 7-letter word, PHARYNX earns the 50-point bingo bonus when played from your rack — that's 72 points from a single turn.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫁 PHARYNX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">22 pts · 7 letters · Throat cavity with X=8, Y=4</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫀 THORAX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · 6 letters · Chest area with X=8, H=4</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🗣️ LARYNX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · 6 letters · Voice box with X=8, Y=4</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">�� KIDNEY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · 6 letters · Filter organ with K=5, Y=4</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💪 ELBOW</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · 5 letters · Joint with W=4, B=3</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🩸 SPLEEN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · 6 letters · Blood organ with common tiles</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Body Words Worth Knowing</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FEMUR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SKULL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WRIST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">THIGH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LYMPH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Body Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X words ending in -YNX:</span> PHARYNX and LARYNX both use the -YNX ending pattern. If holding X and Y together, look for these plays before dumping X on a short word like AX or EX.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PHARYNX as a bingo:</span> At exactly 7 letters, PHARYNX earns the 50-point bingo bonus. Worth 72 points base — more if it hits premium squares. Memorize this as your go-to X bingo.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KIDNEY uses K effectively:</span> K (5pts) is tricky to place. KIDNEY pairs it with common tiles (I, D, N, E, Y) making it one of the most reliable K plays available at 14 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ELBOW for W placement:</span> W (4pts) is often stuck on racks. ELBOW uses W at the end with common letters, scoring 10 points and clearing dead weight from your tiles.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🧠 Anatomy Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Body words with <span class="text-white font-medium">X endings</span> (PHARYNX, THORAX, LARYNX) score 16-22 points base. That's because X=8 combines with H=4 and Y=4 in these medical terms. Learn all three and you'll always have a plan for X.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-science-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Science Words — Lab Vocabulary for High Scores</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-food-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Food Words — Highest Scoring Kitchen Vocabulary</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid body word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
